The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, February 28, 2003 				 Zaheer Abbas dead
																								Burdwan, Feb. 27: Unable to take the twists in the high drama, a first-year student of Kalna College died in front of television during last nights match.																								An avid cricket fan, he was named after stylish Pakistani batsman Zaheer Abbas. He was seeing Souravs boys take on Nasser Hussains England with friends at his Dangapara home. When Kaif ran out Nick Night, we all leapt in joy but Zaheer fell to the floor, writhing in pain. It was all over in minutes, recounted Dola Biswas, one of his friends. Zaheers father said doctors had detected a heart ailment in him some years ago.
